sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant C as Customer (Web/iOS)
  participant BFF as BFF
  participant INV as Store-Inventory Read Svc
  participant CACHE as Redis cache
  participant OMS as OMS Inventory API
  participant RES as Reservation Svc
  participant PG as Aurora Postgres
  participant K as Kafka reservation.events
  participant NF as Notifications / Assoc App

  %% --- 1. PDP inventory read (happy) ---
  rect rgba(0,180,0,0.08)
    Note over C,OMS: PDP inventory read (happy)
    C->>BFF: GET /pdp/{sku}?store=042
    BFF->>INV: GET /inventory?store=042&sku=X
    INV->>CACHE: GET store:042:sku:X
    CACHE-->>INV: qty=3, fetched 8s ago
    INV-->>BFF: {qty: 3, staleness_ms: 8000}
    BFF-->>C: "3 available at Store 042"
  end

  %% --- 2. Reservation (happy) ---
  rect rgba(0,120,200,0.08)
    Note over C,NF: Reservation (happy)
    C->>BFF: POST /reservations (Idempotency-Key)
    BFF->>RES: POST /reservations
    RES->>CACHE: WATCH store:042:sku:X
    RES->>CACHE: DECR qty (MULTI)
    RES->>PG: INSERT reservation (90 min TTL)
    RES->>K: publish reservation.created
    RES-->>BFF: 201 + reservation_id
    BFF-->>C: "Reserved for 90 min"
    K-->>NF: reservation.created
    NF-->>NF: push to associates at store 042
  end

  %% --- 3. Concurrent last-unit reservation ---
  rect rgba(240,120,0,0.08)
    Note over C,PG: Concurrent last-unit (qty=1)
    par Customer A
      C->>RES: POST /reservations (A)
    and Customer B
      C->>RES: POST /reservations (B)
    end
    RES->>CACHE: WATCH/MULTI (A wins)
    RES-->>C: 201 to A
    RES-->>C: 409 to B + alt stores
  end

  %% --- 4. Graceful degradation (OMS down) ---
  rect rgba(200,0,60,0.08)
    Note over C,OMS: Graceful degradation (OMS 5xx)
    C->>BFF: GET /pdp/{sku}
    BFF->>INV: GET /inventory
    INV->>CACHE: miss
    INV->>OMS: call (timeout 800ms)
    OMS-->>INV: 5xx
    INV-->>INV: circuit-breaker OPEN 10s
    INV-->>BFF: {status: unknown, fallback: true}
    BFF-->>C: "Check availability in-store" fallback UI
    Note right of INV: Write path (RES) flag-gated OFF during breaker open
  end
